# UI Polish Mandate (2026-05-22 Master Review)

## Visual Fixes — Exact Values

### 1. Border Radius — NO SHARP CORNERS
| Element | Current | Target |
|---------|---------|--------|
| glass-shell-frame | 2rem | 2rem (OK) |
| neon-glass-card | 1.75rem | 2.25rem |
| neon-glass-card__inner | calc(1.75rem-1px) | calc(2.25rem-1px) |
| buttons, inputs, chips | varies | 9999px (full pill) |
| sidebar | ? | 1.5rem |
| swap form inputs | ? | 1.25rem |

**Rule:** Every visible container, button, input — radius ≥ 1rem. NO rectangular boxes.

### 2. Contrast & Brightness — NO DARK/WASHED OUT
| Setting | Current | Target |
|---------|---------|--------|
| .neon-glass-card__inner bg alpha | 0.35 | 0.22 |
| neon rim glow (cyan) | 0 0 18px rgba(36,247,255,0.35) | 0 0 24px rgba(36,247,255,0.55) |
| neon rim glow (magenta) | 0 0 28px rgba(255,59,212,0.25) | 0 0 32px rgba(255,59,212,0.45) |
| text glow cyan | 0 0 18px rgba(36,247,255,0.65) | 0 0 22px rgba(36,247,255,0.8) |
| text color (headings) | #ffffff | #ffffff (OK) |
| text color (body) | cyan-100/80 | #e0f0ff (brighter) |
| card inner shadow (depth) | 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.18) | inset 0 1px 2px rgba(255,255,255,0.04) |

**Rule:** Cards must feel LUMINOUS, not dark. The aurora galaxy background must be VISIBLE through the glass. If you can't see colors shifting behind the card, the glass is too opaque.

### 3. Glass Clarity — NO MUDDY/BLURRY
| Setting | Current | Target |
|---------|---------|--------|
| backdrop-filter blur | 24px | 16px |
| backdrop-filter saturate | 1.3 | 1.6 |
| background blend mode | normal | normal |
| noise texture overlay | opacity 0.04 | opacity 0.025 |

**Rule:** Glass should add depth without obscuring. 24px blur is too much — reduces to 16px. Saturate up to 1.6x to make colors POP through the glass.

### 4. Card Border Glow — ALL CARDS
Every .neon-glass-card MUST have visible neon rim via ::before pseudo-element:
- border: 1.5px solid rgba(36,247,255,0.3)
- box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(36,247,255,0.55), 0 0 40px rgba(255,59,212,0.35)
- border-radius matching card

### 5. Aurora Galaxy Background
- Boost opacity/particle count by 1.3x
- Speed reduced to 0.7x (calmer, less dizzying)
- Colors: #24f7ff (cyan), #ff3bd4 (magenta), #7c3aed (purple), #00e5ff (teal)

## Missing Features

